.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 22, 2026
.Dt gs\-oldphoto 1
.Os gs\-oldphoto
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm gs\-oldphoto
.Nd applies the GIMP Script\-Fu "Old Photo" filter on an image
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm gs\-oldphoto Ar input\_filename Ar output\_filename
.br
.Op Fl D Ar on|off | Fl Fl defocus Ar on|off
.br
.Op Fl B Ar border\_size | Fl Fl border\-size Ar border\_size
.br
.Op Fl S Ar on|off | Fl Fl sepia Ar on|off
.br
.Op Fl M Ar on|off | Fl Fl mottle Ar on|off
.br
.Op Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
.Op Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
.Nm gs\-oldphoto
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm gs\-oldphoto
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm gs\-oldphoto
runs GIMP to load an image, applies the GIMP Script\-Fu "Old Photo" filter
(details:
.Lk https://docs.gimp.org/3.0/en/script\-fu\-old\-photo.html "GIMP Script\-Fu Old Photo" ) ,
and stores the result into an output file.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar input\_filename
The input image. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected automatically.
.It Ar output\_filename
The name for the output image to be written. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected by the provided file name extension (e.g. .jpeg, .png, .webp, .pdf, ...). An existing output file will be overwritten.
.It Fl D Ar on|off | Fl Fl defocus Ar on|off
Turns defocus on or off. Default: on.
.It Fl B Ar border\_size | Fl Fl border\-size Ar border\_size
Sets the border size for the "Old Photo" filter. Default: 10.
.It Fl S Ar on|off | Fl Fl sepia Ar on|off
Turns sepia on or off. Default: on.
.It Fl M Ar on|off | Fl Fl mottle Ar on|off
Turns mottle on or off. Default: off.
.It Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: suppress GIMP console output. This is the default.
.It Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
Verbose mode: print GIMP console output and processing details.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints the program's command\-line parameters and exits.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints the program version and exits.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It gs\-oldphoto Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-OldPhoto.jpeg
.It gs\-oldphoto Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-OldPhoto\-with\-Border20.jpeg \-\-border\-size 20 \-\-verbose
.It gs\-oldphoto Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-OldPhoto\-with\-Border40.jpeg \-B 40
.It gs\-oldphoto Portobello.jpeg Portobello\-OldPhoto.jpeg \-\-verbose \-\-sepia off \-\-mottle on
.It gs\-oldphoto \-\-help
.It gs\-oldphoto \-h
.It gs\-oldphoto \-\-version
.It gs\-oldphoto \-v
.El
